Responsible Social Media Use, Student Checklist:
  
 Do’s:  
Think before you post. Make sure your content reflects your values and won’t harm your reputation.  
Maintain a professional presence. Keep profiles appropriate, especially on platforms like LinkedIn.  
Verify information before sharing. Avoid spreading misinformation or fake news.  
Use privacy settings wisely. Control who can view your posts and personal details.  
Engage respectfully. Communicate politely, even during disagreements or debates.  
  

Don’ts : 
Don’t overshare personal information. Avoid posting sensitive details like your location, phone number, or private life.  
Don’t post offensive or inappropriate content. It can impact your academic and professional future.  
Don’t engage in online arguments or trolling. It damages your digital image.  
Don’t believe or spread unverified news. Always fact-check before reposting.  
Don’t neglect your time. Avoid excessive scrolling that affects your studies and productivity.  
